  "prompt": "What are some of the very good books for APPSC Group-2 exam?",
  "response": "The **APPSC Group-2 exam** is a highly competitive state-level exam conducted by the Andhra Pradesh Public Service Commission. To excel in this exam, candidates must refer to the right books that cover the syllabus comprehensively. Here are some highly recommended books for the APPSC Group-2 exam:\n\n---\n\n### **1. General Studies**\n- **Andhra Pradesh Economy**:  \n  - *\"Andhra Pradesh Economy\"* by Telugu Akademi  \n  - *\"Indian Economy\"* by Ramesh Singh (Focus on Andhra Pradesh-specific sections)  \n\n- **History of India and Andhra Pradesh**:  \n  - *\"A Brief History of Modern India\"* by Spectrum  \n  - *\"History of Andhra Pradesh\"* by P. Raghunadha Rao  \n\n- **Polity and Governance**:  \n  - *\"Indian Polity\"* by M. Laxmikanth  \n  - *\"Governance in India\"* by M. Laxmikanth  \n\n- **Geography**:  \n  - *\"Certificate Physical and Human Geography\"* by G.C. Leong  \n  - *\"Andhra Pradesh Geography\"* by Telugu Akademi  \n\n- **Environment and Ecology**:  \n  - *\"Environment and Ecology\"* by Shankar IAS Academy  \n  - NCERT Class 11 and 12 (Biology chapters on the environment)  \n\n---\n\n### **2. General Studies - Current Affairs**\n- Monthly Current Affairs Magazines:  \n  - *Pratiyogita Darpan*  \n  - *Chronicle Monthly Magazine*  \n- Yearly Current Affairs Book:  \n  - *\"Manorama Yearbook\"* or *\"Lucent General Knowledge\"*  \n\n---\n\n### **3. Aptitude and Reasoning**\n- *\"Quantitative Aptitude for Competitive Examinations\"* by R.S. Aggarwal  \n- *\"A Modern Approach to Verbal & Non-Verbal Reasoning\"* by R.S. Aggarwal  \n\n---\n\n### **4. English Language Proficiency**\n- *\"Objective General English\"* by S.P. Bakshi  \n- *\"Word Power Made Easy\"* by Norman Lewis (for vocabulary improvement)  \n\n---\n\n### **5. Telugu Language (Optional)**\n- *\"Andhra Pradesh History and Culture\"* by Telugu Akademi  \n- *\"Telugu Vyakaranam\"* (Telugu Grammar) by Telugu Akademi  \n\n---\n\n### **6. Practice Books and Test Series**\n- *\"APPSC Group-2 Previous Year Papers\"* by Arihant Publications  \n- Online Test Series by platforms like **Unacademy**, **Testbook**, or **BYJU's**  \n\n---\n\n### **Additional Resources**\n- NCERT Books (Class 6 to 12) for History, Geography, Polity, and Economy  \n- Andhra Pradesh Government Reports and Publications (for state-specific information)  \n\n---\n\nBy focusing on these books and regularly practicing mock tests, candidates can strengthen their preparation for the APPSC Group-2 exam. Always ensure to stay updated with the latest syllabus and exam pattern. Good luck!",
  "temperature": 1.0,
